meaning:
for the Commonwealth, Golden Wattle, Acacia pycnantha. Although not necessarily official, for the Australian states generally accepted are:-

Western Australia - Kangaroo Paw, Anigosanthos manglesii;

Northern Territory - Blue Waterlily, Nymphaea gigantea or, alternatively, Sturt's Desert Rose, Gossypium sturtianum (Vermilion Gum Eucalyptus miniata also has been proposed);

South Australia - Sturt Pea, Clianthus formosus;

Queensland - Cooktown Orchid, Dendrobium bigibbum;

New South Wales - Waratah, Telopea speciosissima;

Victoria - the heath Epacris impressa (Mountain Ash, Eucalyptus regnans also has been proposed);

Tasmania - Blue Gum, Eucalyptus globulus.
